                <DIV class="ReviewHeading">Description:</DIV>
                <span id="Label1">What starts out as a weekly anonymous tryst between a divorced man and a married woman turns into a searing portrait of loneliness and emotional need. Directed by Patrice Chereau (Queen Margot), INTIMACY won the Golden Bear for Best Film at the 2001 Berlin Film Festival where lead actress Kerry Fox also won the Best Actress Award. Based on Hanif Kureishi&#146;s controversial novel, INTIMACY was selected to play at the Sundance and New York Film Festivals. DVD extras include the original theatrical trailer and cast and filmmaker bios.</span>
              
</td></tr></table>
              <table id="CustomerReviewsPanel" class="ReviewSection" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" border="0" width="100%"><tr><td>
	
